# Knowledge Layer & Learnings

## Knowledge layer overview (Spec 089)

The knowledge layer is the fleet's shared operational brain. Generated by `tools/build_hermes_knowledge_layer.py`.

### Four processing layers

| Layer | Purpose | Output |
|-------|---------|--------|
| Capture | Read-only from specs, artifacts, registry, git, cron | Raw state |
| Normalize | Structured ledgers | artifacts/ops/knowledge_layer/ |
| Reason | Drift, contradiction, missed-run detection | Alerts |
| Deliver | Operator briefs | Daily/weekly summaries |

### Key artifacts

| Artifact | Path | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| latest_state | `artifacts/ops/knowledge_layer/latest_state.{json,md}` | Current fleet operational state |
| held_spec_ledger | `artifacts/ops/held_spec_ledger/latest.{json,md}` | Specifications blocked from proceeding |
| first_fire_ledger | `artifacts/ops/first_fire_ledger/latest.{json,md}` | Items awaiting production validation |
| contradiction_ledger | `artifacts/ops/contradiction_ledger/latest.md` | Known conflicts across sources |
| operator_brief | `artifacts/ops/operator_brief/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Daily ops summary |

### MCP access

```
knowledge_read(artifact="latest_state")
knowledge_read(artifact="held_spec_ledger")
knowledge_read(artifact="contradiction_ledger")
knowledge_read(artifact="operator_brief")
```

## .learnings/ memory system

### Tier structure

| Tier | File | Cap | Update Frequency |
|------|------|-----|-----------------|
| HOT | `.learnings/memory.md` | 100 lines | On significant fleet changes |
| WARM | `.learnings/projects/*.md` | No hard cap | Per-project, on demand |
| COLD | `.learnings/archive/*.md` | — | Demoted from HOT/WARM |

### HOT-tier update triggers

Update `.learnings/memory.md` when:
- Ruleset promoted (new hash active)
- Architecture freeze lifted or imposed
- Major spec closed
- 13F cycle completed
- Model fleet changed (provider migration)
- New agent activated
- Critical agent suppressed/retired

### HOT-tier rules

- Maximum 100 lines (enforce strictly)
- Content: system identity, active ruleset, model fleet, freeze status, blockers, key governance rules
- When at cap: demote oldest entries to WARM tier (`projects/`)
- Bootstrap context only — not automated feedback (Town-Hermes sync FROZEN)

### MCP access

```
learnings_read()                    # HOT tier (memory.md)
learnings_read(file="projects/")    # List WARM tier files
learnings_read(file="projects/<name>.md")  # Specific project memory
```

## Artifacts directory structure

```
artifacts/
  ops/
    knowledge_layer/
      latest_state.json
      latest_state.md
    held_spec_ledger/
      latest.json
      latest.md
    first_fire_ledger/
      latest.json
      latest.md
    contradiction_ledger/
      latest.md
    operator_brief/
      daily/
        YYYY-MM-DD.md
  audit/
    spec_087_b1b_formal_closure_2026_05_14.md
    ...
```

### NTFS junction (Windows/WSL2)

`artifacts/ops/` is a Windows NTFS directory junction -> `C:\Projects\biotech_screener\biotech-screener\artifacts\ops\`

This means:
- `knowledge_read()` resolves against live biotech-screener production artifacts
- Nightly cron runs auto-update through the junction
- No manual copy step needed

## Contradiction handling

When contradictions are found:
1. Log in contradiction_ledger (do NOT silently resolve)
2. Classify: hard contradiction (blocks operations) vs possible drift (investigation needed)
3. Escalate hard contradictions to operator
4. Possible drift: investigate in next available session

## Anti-patterns

- Do NOT write to .learnings/ via automation (Town-Hermes feedback FROZEN)
- Do NOT exceed 100-line HOT-tier cap (demote, don't extend)
- Do NOT resolve contradictions without logging — silent resolution = governance violation
- Do NOT assume artifact files exist — check gracefully, return structured errors